article_title: Police investigate student suicide on K-State campus
article_text:
Kansas State University police is investigating the apparent suicide of a student who was found on the campus Saturday morning.

KSU police were called around 11:10 a.m. to the report of a possible dead person in a parking lot on campus. Officers found a male student in a vehicle with a self-inflicted gunshot wound.

The student's name was not released.
